<tool id="show_projection" name="Makes a projection" version="0.0.1">
  <description>from a 3D synthetic image.</description>
  <command interpreter="bash">
    show_projection.sh $input $channel
  </command>
  <inputs>
    <param format="zip" name="input" type="data" label="3D image"></param>
    <param name="channel" type="integer" value="1" label="Select channel index" />
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="png" name="output" from_work_dir="output.png"/>
  </outputs>
<help>

**Description**

Makes a projection from one channel of a 3D synthetic image. This projection can be opened in a web browser.

-----

**Input**

A 3D synthetic image.

-----

**Output**

A PNG file.
</help>
</tool>
